entries.entry: Our team worked a lot with Git and GitHub commands.
Worked on a few different projects, including Martin's Aquarium and Modern Farm.
Still working on Martin's Aquarium and Modern Farm.

Working again with Event Listeners and a local API. It is starting to make a lot more sense now that I have used it quite a bit more. Also getting used to modularizing my code, particularly JavaScript. Additionally, I have been keeping in mind the importance of de-coupling when possible (This is the process of keeping code relevant to a certain functionality nearly or completely separate from other code and only allowing anonymous communication via eventListeners.
